# Line endings are LF in the repository and LF in every working tree, whatever
# the contributor's platform or their `core.autocrlf` setting. Without this, a
# Windows checkout rewrites text files to CRLF on the way out and back, which
# turns every review into a diff of invisible characters.
#
# `text=auto` lets git decide what is text by content; `eol=lf` then pins the
# working-tree form. Files listed as `binary` are exempt from both, so no byte of
# a font, an image or a fixture document is ever touched.
* text=auto eol=lf

*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.webp  binary
*.ico   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.docx  binary
*.pdf   binary
